ted the band The Tender Trio with Rene Lopez and Royston Langdon of [[Spacehog]] fame.  The band broke up in March 2006.\n\nStevens has stated that he plays guitar and paints in his free time.  He also has a daughter<ref name=\"Clarke\"/> and a son.\n\nStevens recently graduated from the University of Pennsylvania School of Law.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.facebook.com/rogersstevens?sk=info |title=Rogers Stevens |publisher=Facebook.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> In December 2014, he was reported to be an associate in the labor and employment group of Philadelphia law firm Ballard Spahr.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abajournal.com/news/article/after_a_career_change_blind_melon_guitarist_is_a_biglaw_lawyer/ |title=After a career change, Blind Melon guitarist is a BigLaw lawyer\n |publisher=abajournal.com |accessdate=2014-12-18}}</ref>  He is now an associate in the Labor and Employment group of Philadelphia law firm Pepper Hamilton LLP.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===With Blind Melon===\nStudio Albums:\n*''[[Blind Melon (album)|Blind Melon]], 1992\n*''[[Soup (Blind Melon album)|Soup]], 1995\n*''[[Nico (album)|Nico]], 1996\n*''[[Classic Masters (Blind Melon album)|Classic Masters (Blind Melon)]], 2002\n*''[[Live At The Palace|Live At the Palace]], 2006\n*''[[For My Friends]], 2008\n\nEPs/Demos\n*''Sippin' Time Sessions (Unreleased EP), 1991\n\n===With Extra Virgin===\nStudio Albums:\n*''Twelve Stories High, 2000\n\nEPs/Demos:\n*''First Cold Pressing (Demo), 1999\n*''Rock City (Unreleased Demo), 2002\n\n===With The Tender Trio===\nEPs/Demos:\n*''Hamburger Demos'' (Demo), 2004<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beemelon.com |title=Blind Melon fan site |language=fr |publisher=BeeMelon.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Blind Melon}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stevens, Rogers}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Alternative rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:American alternative rock musicians]]\n[[Category:America